    <span class='add'>Screenshot set edit mode</span>

    <p>
     There are two ways to set a document in
     <a href='../concepts/edit_mode.html'>edit mode</a>:
   </p>

   <ol>
    <li>Clicking on the 'edit' button in <a href='../concepts/review_mode.html'>review mode</a>.
     If you do not see an edit button on an existing document, you probably have no permission
     to edit the document. In the standard configuration, only the one who created the document
     may edit it later. Even the
     <a href='../../cms_admins/index.html'>CMS administrator</a> may not
     edit a document in the CMS that
     was created by someone else. However, he always can via the
     <a href='http://www.onehippo.org/site-toolkit/misc/content+repository/using+web+console.html'>web console</a>.
     <a href='../../cms_admins/howto/set_permissions_for_group.html'>Permissions can be configured by the
     CMS administrator</a>.
    </li>
    <li><a href='./create_document.html'>Creating a new document</a>. The new, empty document will
     immediately be presented in <a href='../concepts/edit_mode.html'>edit mode</a>, 
     as not many would need <a href='../concepts/review_mode.html'>review mode</a> for an empty document.
    </li>
   </ol>

